    {
      "id": "PopularPost133746",
      "post_content": "Alright, is there a slower card with this much power in the game? It took me about 5 tries to win with my hibernation deck, and it was totally worth it. A challenging, but fun card to build around.   \nUse [Braid of Fire](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Braid of Fire) to power it and the firebreathers you pluck. As long as you have those two cards, grab a [shard phoenix](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=shard phoenix) and go crazy.   \nIt is so slow that you need a way to prevent your opponent from overwhelming you before you can get any power on the board. Try using all fliers (including birds of paradise for your first hibernation drop) and [fault line](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=fault line)s to keep them at bay. If you can get up to a [scourge of kher ridges](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=scourge of kher ridges), then you must have succeeded enough and the game will be yours.   \n2nd flying hibernation drop: arcbound stinger  \n3rd drop: Chandra's Spitfire (good with fault lines in multi-player)  \n4th drop: furnace/dragon whelp  \nAfter that the choices for killer fliers are practically endless.   \n  ",
      "posted_by": "kiseki",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost133746\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_post\">Alright, is there a slower card with this much power in the game?  It took me about 5 tries to win with my hibernation deck, and it was totally worth it.  A challenging, but fun card to build around.  <br/>Use <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Braid of Fire\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Braid of Fire\">Braid of Fire</a> to power it and the firebreathers you pluck.  As long as you have those two cards, grab a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"shard phoenix\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=shard phoenix\">shard phoenix</a> and go crazy.  <br/>It is so slow that you need a way to prevent your opponent from overwhelming you before you can get any power on the board.  Try using all fliers (including birds of paradise for your first hibernation drop) and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"fault line\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=fault line\">fault line</a>s to keep them at bay.  If you can get up to a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"scourge of kher ridges\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=scourge of kher ridges\">scourge of kher ridges</a>, then you must have succeeded enough and the game will be yours.  <br/>2nd flying hibernation drop: arcbound stinger<br/>3rd drop: Chandra's Spitfire (good with fault lines in multi-player)<br/>4th drop: furnace/dragon whelp<br/>After that the choices for killer fliers are practically endless.  <br/><br/></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '133746'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy51522\">kiseki</span>\r\n                                (2/1/2011 2:59:15 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>"
